oney is, legally, a stretch for the SEC. The Department of Justice can go a=
fter the exchange for=C2=A0wire fraud, and the CFTC can go after a crypto f=
utures exchange for commodity futures fraud, but the SEC might feel a bit l=
eft out.
Unless the crypto exchange sold=C2=A0stock. If the crypto exchange raised m=
oney from=C2=A0investors=C2=A0by selling them=C2=A0stock, well, the stock i=
s clearly a security. And if it didn=E2=80=99t=C2=A0tell=C2=A0the investors=
, as it sold them the stock, =E2=80=9Chey by the way we are stealing money =
from our customers,=E2=80=9D then the investors were defrauded.=C2=A0
