   =20
      Wirefraud
   =20
 =20

I don=E2=80=99t know how true  this is =E2=80=94=C2=A0Bankman-Fried denied =
it, and it sounds sort of too good to be true =E2=80=94=C2=A0but it is enou=
gh up my alley that I have to pass it along:

Members of the inner circle of power at collapsed cryptocurrency exchange F=
TX formed a chat group called "Wirefraud" and were using it to send secret =
information about operations in the lead up to the company's spectacular fa=
ilure.
On the eve of the first big hearing in the US Congress this week that will =
investigate FTX's collapse, The Australian Financial Review has learnt that=
 FTX founders Sam Bankman-Fried and Zixiao =E2=80=9CGary=E2=80=9D Wang, alo=
ng with FTX engineer Nishad Singh and former Alameda Research chief executi=
ve Caroline Ellison, used a chat group on Signal in the hope that the infor=
mation would remain hidden.
On Monday (Tuesday AEDT) Mr Bankman-Fried denied being part of the chat say=
ing, =E2=80=9CIf this is true then I wasn't a member of that inner circle (=
I'm quite sure it's just false; I have never heard of such a group).=E2=80=
=9D

Don=E2=80=99t =E2=80=A6=C2=A0don=E2=80=99t name your group chat Wirefraud? =
I mean I guess if you work for the US Attorney=E2=80=99s office you can do =
it, but even then I might go with =E2=80=9CStoppingwirefraud=E2=80=9D just =
to be safe.

 =20
   =20
      Put spreads
   =20
 =20

I=20
wrote yesterday that =E2=80=9Cbig serious players in crypto are long crypto=
 volatility at a small scale, but short crypto volatility at a large scale,=
=E2=80=9D and: =E2=80=9CYou are long a put spread I guess.=E2=80=9D Like th=
ree people emailed to point out that really I mean a ratio put spread: You =
make money if stuff goes down a little, but=C2=A0lose=C2=A0money if it goes=
 down a lot, which is not true of a simple 1-to-1 put spread. I appreciate =
that my readers care about the specifics of derivatives metaphors.

